npm install express
npm install typescript @types/node @types/express ts-node --save-dev

express: The Express framework.
typescript: TypeScript compiler.
@types/node: Type definitions for Node.js.
@types/express: Type definitions for Express.
ts-node: TypeScript execution environment for Node.js.



npx tsc --init

Creates a tsconfig.json file to configure TypeScript:
{
  "compilerOptions": {
    "target": "ES2020",
    "module": "commonjs",
    "outDir": "./dist",
    "rootDir": "./src",
    "strict": true,
    "esModuleInterop": true,
    "skipLibCheck": true,
    "forceConsistentCasingInFileNames": true
  },
  "include": ["src/**/*.ts"],
  "exclude": ["node_modules"]
}

target: Sets the JavaScript language version to which TypeScript will be compiled.
module: Specifies the module code generation method.
outDir: The directory where compiled JavaScript files will be output.
rootDir: The directory containing the TypeScript source files.
strict: Enables all strict type-checking options.


